 4\n| seats3         = 8\n| seats_after3   = \n| seat_change3   = {{increase}}4\n| popular_vote3  = '''13,741'''\n| percentage3    = '''33.9%'''\n\n<!--Lib Dems-->\n| image4         = [[File:No image wide.svg|115x50px|Blank]]\n| party4         = Scottish Liberal Democrats\n| leader4        = Ben Lawrie\n| leaders_seat4  = [[Monifieth and Sidlaw (ward)|Monifieth and Sidlaw]]\n| last_election4 = ''3 seat, 10.3%''\n| seats_before4  = 1\n| seats_needed4  = {{increase}}14\n| seats4         = 2\n| seat_change4   = {{increase}}1\n| popular_vote4  = 1,873\n| percentage4    = 4.6%\n\n<!--       Labour       -->\n| image5         = [[File:No image wide.svg|115x50px|Blank]]\n| leader5        = Margaret Thomson\n| party5         = Scottish Labour Party\n| leaders_seat5  = [[Monifieth and Sidlaw (ward)|Monifieth and Sidlaw]] (''retired'')\n| last_election5 = ''2 seats, 6.9%''\n| seats_before5  = 1\n| seats_needed5  = {{increase}}14\n| seats5         = 0\n| seats_after5   = \n| seat_change5   = {{decrease}}1\n| popular_vote5  = 2,178\n| percentage5    = 5.4%\n\n| map_image = Angus Council election 2017.svg\n| map_size = \n| map_alt = \n| map = \n| map_caption = The multi-member wards\n\n<!-- bottom -->\n| title           = Council Leader\n| before_election = Iain Gaul\n| before_party    = Scottish National Party\n| posttitle       = Council Leader after election\n| after_election  = Bob Myles\n| after_party     = Independent (politician)\n}}\n\nElections to [[Angus Council]] were held on 4 May 2017, the same day as the other [[Local government in Scotland|Scottish local government]] [[2012 Scottish local elections|elections]]. The election used the eight [[ward (politics)|wards]], created under the [[Local Governance (Scotland) Act 2004]], with each ward electing three or four councillors using the [[single transferable vote]] system, a form of [[proportional representation]]. A total of 28 councillors were elected, one less than in 2012.\n\nFollowing the 2012{{clarify|date=February 2020}} election the Scottish National Party formed the administration on the Council. Cllr Ian Gaul (Kirriemuir and Dean) was appointed Leader of the Council at the subsequent statutory meeting; Cllr Paul Valentine (Montrose) became [[Deputy|Depute]]{{Disambiguation needed|date=April 2020}} Leader; and Cllr Helen Oswald (Carnoustie and District) was elected Provost.\n\n==Election result==\n\n{{Election Summary Begin|title = Angus Local Election Result 2017}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Scottish National Party\n  |seats      = 9\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 6\n  |net        = -6\n  |seats %    = 32.1\n  |votes %    = 31.2\n  |votes      = 12,657\n  |plus/minus = -13.2\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Independent (politician)\n  |seats      = 9\n  |gain       = 1\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = +1\n  |seats %    = 32.1\n  |votes %    = 25.0\n  |votes      = 10,144\n  |plus/minus = +0.2\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Scottish Conservative Party\n  |seats      = 8\n  |gain       = +4\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = +4\n  |seats %    = 28.6\n  |votes %    = 33.9\n  |votes      = 13,741\n  |plus/minus = +16.1\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Scottish Liberal Democrats\n  |seats      = 2\n  |gain       = 2\n  |loss       = 1\n  |net        = +1\n  |seats %    = 7.1\n  |votes %    = 4.6\n  |votes      = 1,873\n  |plus/minus = -1.2\n}}\n{{Election Summary Party|\n  |party      = Scottish Labour Party\n  |seats      = 0\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 1\n  |net        = -1\n  |seats %    = 0\n  |votes %    = 5.4\n  |votes      = 2,178\n  |plus/minus = -2.0\n}}\n\n{{Election box end}}\n<small>'''Note:''' \"Votes\" are the first preference votes. The net gain/loss and percentage changes relate to the result of the previous Scottish local elections on 3 May 2012. This may differ from other published sources showing gain/loss relative to seats held at dissolution of Scotland's councils.</small><