ck]] [[Groove (music)|grooves]], [[country rock]] and balladry,<ref name=\"guardian\">Simpson, Dave. \"[https://www.theguardian.com/music/2005/jan/21/popandrock.shopping5 Julian Cope, Citizen Cain'd review]\". [[The Guardian]]. 21 January 2005. Retrieved on 27 March 2018.</ref><ref name=\"uncut\">Goddard, Simon. \"[http://www.uncut.co.uk/reviews/album/julian-cope-citizen-caind Julian Cope \u2013 Citizen Cain\u2019d review]\". [[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]. 25 February 2005. Retrieved on 27 March 2018.</ref><ref name=\"headheritage\">[http://www.headheritage.co.uk/citizencaind/ Head Heritage - Citizen Cain'd] Headheritage.co.uk. Retrieved 27 March 2018</ref> ''Citizen Cain'd'' has been described as \"an excellent return to song-based songwriting\"<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web |first=James |last=Mason |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r731743 |pure_url=yes}}|title=Julian Cope \u2013 ''Citizen Cain'd'': Review |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=27 March 2018}}</ref> and \"best Cope album in a decade\".<ref name=\"uncut\">Goddard, Simon. \"[http://www.uncut.co.uk/reviews/album/julian-cope-citizen-caind Julian Cope \u2013 Citizen Cain\u2019d review]\". [[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]. 25 February 2005. Retrieved on 27 March 2018.</ref> \n\n==Track listing==\n\n{{tracklist\n| all_writing     = \n| collapsed       = no\n| headline        =Disc one\n| total_length    = 34:42\n| title1          = Hell Is Wicked\n| length1         = 4:42\n| title2          = I Can't Hardly Stand It\n| length2         = 3:10\n| title3          = I'm Living In The Room They Found Saddam In \n| length3         = 4:26\n| title4          = Gimme Head\n| length4         = 3:49\n| title5          = Dying to Meet You\n| length5         = 4:46\n| title6          = I Will Be Absorbed\n| length6         = 13:47\n}}\n\n{{tracklist\n| all_writing     = \n| collapsed       = no\n| headline        =Disc two\n| total_length    = 36:56 (71:38)\n| title1          = Feels Like a Crying Shame\n| length1         = 11:32\n|